                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, Aug. 17 (PTI): The government today said there was a shortage of about 1,350 IPS officers because additional posts were sanctioned after cadre reviews.          Minister of state for home Ajay Maken said the shortage was having a bearing on filling up of senior police positions in the states and at the Centre. He said training facilities were being improved for police personnel at all levels and mandatory mid-career training programmes introduced.                  
	Lucknow: Commando Kanaiya Yadavs headless body was found by police near a Chhattisgarh highway on Saturday. He was part of 204 Cobra battalion of the CRPF. Yadav, 38, had boarded a train for Bastar on August 12. He was on a bus that was stopped by suspected Maoists on the night of August 13. The rebels made all the passengers get off and singled out Yadav though he was not in uniform. The body was identified on the basis of an identity card and driving licence.                  
	 Bhopal (PTI): Around 1,400 junior doctors in Madhya Pradesh went on an indefinite strike on Tuesday demanding compensation of Rs 25 lakh to family members of two medical students who were crushed to death by a police van on Sunday.                  
	Jaipur (PTI): Over 34.69 lakh voters will decide the fate of 10,132 candidates on Wednesday in polls to 126 civic bodies in Rajasthan. Over 35,000 electronic voting machines are being used for the polls.
                                                                                                                                              
